This is a linux kernel driver for ADC (analog-to-digital converter) available
over at91 SoC family.

For more info on the use see the code or:
	http://www.acmesystems.it/?id=foxg20_adc

CROSS-COMPILE
-------------
To cross-compile this driver you need a gcc-arm and configured kernel. Then
simple type:

make KERNELDIR=<path_to_kernel> CROSSCOMPILE=<path to ggc cross compiler>

This will generate at91-adc.ko that can be loaded on your linux board 
using insmod.

